  "body": "Follow the investigations in [fixing new transactions never show PR](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/pull/7527) which found that pending transactions don't appear in the Activity tab view. They are visible only after a restart or when the next 20-minute cycle updates the transaction history for all the wallet accounts.\r\n\r\nAlso, it was found that the cyclic 20 minutes blocks the UI\r\n\r\nThe following consideration are to be addressed for an improved user experience:\r\n\r\n- [ ] Show pending transactions in the activity view as soon as the send dialog goes away\r\n- [ ] Don't block UI when updating all the transactions\r\n  - Given that the call `checkRecentHistory` which executes RPC call `wallet_checkRecentHistoryForChainIDs` doesn't return or wait for the processing to be done investigate which of the solutions are optimal to implement\r\n    - Run async `checkRecentHistory` if the RPC call is blocking until the results are updated\r\n    - Address signal manager updates if they are the culprit",
